            . I am the wife of William Gilling - we live in <placeName id="t18260914-261-crimeloc1487">Cow-cross-street, Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-261-crimeloc1487" type="placeName" value="Cow-cross-street, Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-261-crimeloc1487" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-261-off1485 t18260914-261-crimeloc1487"></join>. I let the prisoner, on the 24th of April, a furnished room, on the second floor, at 6s. per week; he stated he was married, and he brought a woman with him - they remained till the 10th of August; his wife asked me for a clean pair of sheets, which I gave her, and in about half an hour I saw her go out with something under her apron; I watched her to the pawnbroker's; the prisoner was at home at that time, out of work; I am confident he was in their room, it was between eleven and twelve o'clock in the day.</p>
